------------------------------------------------------------------------
SECTION 4: WEIL BOUND -- FROBENIUS EIGENVALUE NONZERO
------------------------------------------------------------------------

For ALL newforms f in S_2(Gamma_0(N)), Deligne's theorem (1974) gives:
  alpha_{2,f} * beta_{2,f} = 2  (weight-2, prime p=2)
  |alpha_{2,f}| = |beta_{2,f}| = sqrt(2)  (Riemann Hypothesis for curves)

Since alpha * beta = 2 > 0 and p = 2 > 0, BOTH Frobenius eigenvalues
are necessarily nonzero for ALL newforms f at ALL prime levels N.
(This holds for ANY prime p ≠ N, using alpha * beta = p > 0.)

      N  gcd(2,N)  Frobenius product  Eigenvalues nonzero?
     67         1  alpha*beta = 2          YES (Weil bound)
     73         1  alpha*beta = 2          YES (Weil bound)
    103         1  alpha*beta = 2          YES (Weil bound)
    107         1  alpha*beta = 2          YES (Weil bound)
    167         1  alpha*beta = 2          YES (Weil bound)
    191         1  alpha*beta = 2          YES (Weil bound)
    193         1  alpha*beta = 2          YES (Weil bound)
    223         1  alpha*beta = 2          YES (Weil bound)
    227         1  alpha*beta = 2          YES (Weil bound)
    229         1  alpha*beta = 2          YES (Weil bound)
    269         1  alpha*beta = 2          YES (Weil bound)

Conclusion: T_2 has ALL NONZERO eigenvalues on H^{1,0}(J_0(N))
for all 11 PREDICT_FAIL primes.  [VERIFIED by Weil bound]

------------------------------------------------------------------------
SECTION 5: GENUS COMPUTATION (DIAMOND-SHURMAN THM 3.1.1)
------------------------------------------------------------------------

Formula (exact integer arithmetic):
  eps2 = 1 + Leg(-1, N)   [0 if N=3 mod 4; 2 if N=1 mod 4]
  eps3 = 1 + Leg(-3, N)   [0 if N=2 mod 3; 2 if N=1 mod 3]
  12*g = (N+1) - 3*eps2 - 4*eps3

