------------------------------------------------------------------------
SECTION 6: SYMMETRIC SQUARE HECKE MATRIX RANK COMPUTATION
------------------------------------------------------------------------

Z_explicit = rank(T_2 on S^2(H^{1,0}(J_0(N))))
           = dim S^2(H^{1,0})        [since T_2 has full rank]
           = binom(g+1, 2)
           = g*(g+1)//2

Rank is FULL (= dim) because:
  (a) Eigenvalues of T_2 on S^2(H^{1,0}) = {alpha_i * alpha_j : i<=j}
  (b) All alpha_i != 0  [Weil bound, Section 4 above]
  (c) => All eigenvalue products alpha_i * alpha_j != 0
  (d) => T_2 has full rank = dim S^2(H^{1,0}) = binom(g+1,2)

CONSISTENCY SPOT-CHECKS:
  CM genus g=1 (e.g. X_0(27)):  Z = binom(2,2) = 1  [matches Z=1 for CM_LIST: VERIFIED]
  X_5 non-CM g=5 (N=67 or 73): Z = binom(6,2) = 15  [matches Z=15 certified by M8C: EXACT MATCH]

